The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 13 March is 40,805 (4,722.9 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 08 March, there were 296 new confirmed cases (34.3 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 01 March, there were 424 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 30% (128 fewer cases).
